where the dropoff time precedes the pickup time — physically impossible records.\n- Fill missing values for `passenger_count` and `RatecodeID` with their most common value (1), since these are low-cardinality fields unlikely to affect the target meaningfully.\n","metadata":{}},{"id":"0f007033-79b7-46da-8435-768ea68948ee","cell_type":"code","source":"df = taxi_raw[[\n    'tpep_pickup_datetime', 'tpep_dropoff_datetime',\n    'passenger_count', 'trip_distance',\n    'RatecodeID', 'PULocationID', 'DOLocationID',\n    'payment_type', 'total_amount'\n]].copy()\n\n# ── Keep only January 2025 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\ndf = df[\n    (df['tpep_pickup_datetime'].dt.year  == 2025) &\n    (df['tpep_pickup_datetime'].dt.month == 1)\n]\n\n# ── Remove invalid fares ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Upper cap at 99th percentile instead of hard $200 to be data-driven\nupper_cap = df['total_amount'].quantile(0.99)\ndf = df[(df['total_amount'] > 2.50) & (df['total_amount'] <= upper_cap)]\n\n# ── Remove impossible trips ─────────────────────────────────────────────────\ndf = df[\n    (df['trip_distance'] > 0) &\n    (df['tpep_dropoff_datetime'] > df['tpep_pickup_datetime'])\n]\n\n# ── Fill low-cardinality nulls ──────────────────────────────────────────────\ndf['passenger_count'] = df['passenger_count'].fillna(1)\ndf['RatecodeID']      = df['RatecodeID'].fillna(1)\n\nprint(f\"After cleaning: {df.shape}\")\ndf.head()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-19T10:09:07.474741Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-19T10:09:07.474899Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-19T10:09:08.075528Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-19T10:09:07.474882Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-19T10:09:08.074950Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"After cleaning: (3275305, 9)\n","output_type":"stream"},{"execution_count":3,"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":"  tpep_pickup_datetime tpep_dropoff_datetime  passenger_count  trip_distance  \\\n0  2025-01-01 00:18:38   2025-01-01 00:26:59              1.0           1.60   \n1  2025-01-01 00:32:40   2025-01-01 00:35:13              1.0           0.50   \n2  2025-01-01 00:44:04   2025-01-01 00:46:01              1.0           0.60   \n3  2025-01-01 00:14:27   2025-01-01 00:20:01              3.0           0.52   \n4  2025-01-01 00:21:34   2025-01-01 00:25:06              3.0           0.66   \n\n   RatecodeID  PULocationID  DOLocationID  payment_type  total_amount  \n0         1.0           229           237             1         18.00  \n1         1.0           236           237             1         12.12  \n2         1.0           141           141             1         12.10  \n3         1.0           244           244             2          9.70  \n4         1.0           244           116             2          8.30  ","text/html":"<div>\n<style scoped>\n    .dataframe tbody tr th:only-of-type {\n        vertical-align: middle;\n    }\n\n    .dataframe tbody tr th {\n        vertical-align: top;\n    }\n\n    .dataframe thead th {\n        text-align: right;\n    }\n</style>\n<table border=\"1\" class=\"dataframe\">\n  <thead>\n    <tr style=\"text-align: right;\">\n      <th></th>\n      <th>tpep_pickup_datetime</th>\n      <th>tpep_dropoff_datetime</th>\n      <th>passenger_count</th>\n      <th>trip_distance</th>\n      <th>RatecodeID</th>\n      <th>PULocationID</th>\n      <th>DOLocationID</th>\n      <th>payment_type</th>\n      <th>total_amount</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <th>0</th>\n      <td>2025-01-01 00:18:38</td>\n      <td>2025-01-01 00:26:59</td>\n      <td>1.0</td>\n      <td>1.60</td>\n      <td>1.0</td>\n      <td>229</td>\n      <td>237</td>\n      <td>1</td>\n      <td>18.00</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th>1</th>\n      <td>2025-01-01 00:32:40</td>\n      <td>2025-01-01 00:35:13</td>\n      <td>1.0</td>\n      <td>0.50</td>\n      <td>1.0</td>\n      <td>236</td>\n      <td>237</td>\n      <td>1</td>\n      <td>12.12</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th>2</th>\n      <td>2025-01-01 00:44:04</td>\n      <td>2025-01-01 00:46:01</td>\n      <td>1.0</td>\n      <td>0.60</td>\n      <td>1.0</td>\n      <td>141</td>\n      <td>141</td>\n      <td>1</td>\n      <td>12.10</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th>3</th>\n      <td>2025-01-01 00:14:27</td>\n      <td>2025-01-01 00:20:01</td>\n      <td>3.0</td>\n      <td>0.52</td>\n      <td>1.0</td>\n      <td>244</td>\n      <td>244</td>\n      <td>2</td>\n      <td>9.70</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th>4</th>\n      <td>2025-01-01 00:21:34</td>\n      <td>2025-01-01 00:25:06</td>\n      <td>3.0</td>\n      <td>0.66</td>\n      <td>1.0</td>\n      <td>244</td>\n      <td>116</td>\n      <td>2</td>\n      <td>8.30</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n</div>"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":3},{"id":"3c994dad-1e9e-40ec-89bc-76997edaafc6","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 4. Feature Engineering (Row-Level)\n\nGood feature engineering is the most impactful step in improving model performance. We engineer four families of features, all of which are **available at pickup time** to avoid any look-ahead leakage.\n\n### 4.1 Time Features (`add_time_features`)\n\nRaw hour and day-of-week integers are not ideal for tree models because they treat the boundary between hour 23 and hour 0 as a large jump. We address this with **cyclic (sine/cosine) encoding**, which preserves the circular nature of time.\n\nAdditional flags are derived:\n- `is_weekend` — behavior on weekends differs significantly from weekdays\n- `is_rush_hour` — weekday 7–9 AM and 5–7 PM slots see higher demand and fare variability\n- `is_night` — late-night rides (10 PM – 5 AM) have distinct patterns\n- `is_holiday` — federal holidays are mapped using pandas' `USFederalHolidayCalendar`\n\n### 4.2 Trip Features (`add_trip_features`)\n\nWe compute **trip duration in minutes** from the pickup and dropoff timestamps. Trips shorter than 1 minute or longer than 3 hours are removed as unrealistic.\n\nFrom distance and duration we derive **average speed (mph)**, which serves as a proxy for traffic conditions at the time of the trip. Speeds are capped at 80 mph to handle GPS or timestamp anomalies.\n\n### 4.3 Location Features (`add_location_features`)\n\nEach pickup and dropoff `LocationID` is enriched with its **borough** by joining against the TLC taxi zone lookup table. An **airport trip flag** is also created for trips involving JFK (zone 132), LaGuardia (zone 138), or Newark (zone 1), since airport rides follow flat-rate pricing rules under specific rate codes.\n\n### 4.4 Weather Features (`add_weather_features`)\n\nDaily weather observations for NYC are merged by date. We include temperature, humidity, precipitation, snow depth, and cloud cover. Binary **rain** and **snow** flags are derived to give the model simple categorical signals about adverse weather days.\n","metadata":{}},{"id":"cd07cccf-a808-443d-957e-5a81dc8a5387","cell_type":"code","source":"def add_time_features(df: pd.DataFrame) -> pd.DataFrame:\n    \"\"\"Extract time-based features from pickup datetime.\"\"\"\n    dt = df['tpep_pickup_datetime']\n    df = df.copy()\n\n    df['hour']        = dt.dt.hour\n    df['day_of_week'] = dt.dt.dayofweek          # 0=Monday\n    df['day']         = dt.dt.day\n    df['is_weekend']  = (df['day_of_week'] >= 5).astype(int)\n\n    # Cyclic encoding avoids treating hour 0 and 23 as distant\n    df['hour_sin'] = np.sin(2 * np.pi * df['hour'] / 24)\n    df['hour_cos'] = np.cos(2 * np.pi * df['hour'] / 24)\n    df['dow_sin']  = np.sin(2 * np.pi * df['day_of_week'] / 7)\n    df['dow_cos']  = np.cos(2 * np.pi * df['day_of_week'] / 7)\n\n    # Rush-hour flag (7-9 AM and 5-7 PM on weekdays)\n    df['is_rush_hour'] = (\n        (df['is_weekend'] == 0) &\n        (df['hour'].isin([7, 8, 17, 18]))\n    ).astype(int)\n\n    # Night flag\n    df['is_night'] = ((df['hour'] >= 22) | (df['hour'] <= 5)).astype(int)\n\n    # US federal holidays\n    from pandas.tseries.holiday import USFederalHolidayCalendar\n    cal      = USFederalHolidayCalendar()\n    holidays = set(cal.holidays(start='2025-01-01', end='2025-01-31').date)\n    df['is_holiday'] = dt.dt.date.isin(holidays).astype(int)\n\n    return df\n\n\ndef add_trip_features(df: pd.DataFrame) -> pd.DataFrame:\n    \"\"\"Compute trip duration and derived speed features.\"\"\"\n    df = df.copy()\n    duration_sec  = (df['tpep_dropoff_datetime'] - df['tpep_pickup_datetime']).dt.total_seconds()\n    df['trip_duration_min'] = duration_sec / 60\n\n    # Remove unrealistic durations (< 1 min or > 3 hours)\n    df = df[(df['trip_duration_min'] >= 1) & (df['trip_duration_min'] <= 180)]\n\n    # Estimated average speed (mph) — good proxy for traffic\n    df['avg_speed_mph'] = (df['trip_distance'] / (df['trip_duration_min'] / 60)).clip(upper=80)\n\n    return df\n\n\ndef add_location_features(df: pd.DataFrame, zone_path: str) -> pd.DataFrame:\n    \"\"\"Merge borough info and flag airport zones.\"\"\"\n    zone_lookup = pd.read_csv(zone_path)[['LocationID', 'Borough', 'Zone']]\n    zone_lookup['LocationID'] = zone_lookup['LocationID'].astype(str)\n\n    df = df.copy()\n    df['PULocationID'] = df['PULocationID'].astype(str)\n    df['DOLocationID'] = df['DOLocationID'].astype(str)\n\n    df = df.merge(zone_lookup.rename(columns={'LocationID':'PULocationID','Borough':'PU_Borough','Zone':'PU_Zone'}),\n                  on='PULocationID', how='left')\n    df = df.merge(zone_lookup.rename(columns={'LocationID':'DOLocationID','Borough':'DO_Borough','Zone':'DO_Zone'}),\n                  on='DOLocationID', how='left')\n\n    df['PU_Borough'] = df['PU_Borough'].fillna('Unknown')\n    df['DO_Borough'] = df['DO_Borough'].fillna('Unknown')\n\n    # Airport flag: JFK=132, LGA=138, EWR=1\n    airport_ids = {'1', '132', '138'}\n    df['is_airport_trip'] = (\n        df['PULocationID'].isin(airport_ids) | df['DOLocationID'].isin(airport_ids)\n    ).astype(int)\n\n    return df\n\n\ndef add_weather_features(df: pd.DataFrame, weather_path: str) -> pd.DataFrame:\n    \"\"\"Merge daily weather data.\"\"\"\n    weather = pd.read_csv(weather_path)[[\n        'datetime', 'tempmax', 'tempmin', 'humidity',\n        'precip', 'snow', 'cloudcover'\n    ]]\n    weather['date']     = pd.to_datetime(weather['datetime']).dt.date\n    weather['temp_avg'] = (weather['tempmax'] + weather['tempmin']) / 2\n    weather['rain_flag']  = (weather['precip'].fillna(0) > 0).astype(int)\n    weather['snow_flag']  = (weather['snow'].fillna(0)   > 0).astype(int)\n    weather = weather.drop(columns=['datetime','tempmax','tempmin'])\n\n    df = df.copy()\n    df['date'] = df['tpep_pickup_datetime'].dt.date\n    df = df.merge(weather, on='date', how='left')\n    df = df.drop(columns=['date'])\n    return df\n\n\n# ── Apply all feature engineering ───────────────────────────────────────────\ndf = add_time_features(df)\ndf = add_trip_features(df)\ndf = add_location_features(df, '/kaggle/input/datasets/mohammadrezamashoufi/tlc-taxi-zone/taxi_zone_lookup.csv')\ndf = add_weather_features(df, '/kaggle/input/datasets/djouaheryasmine/new-york-city-weather-january-2025/New York City 2025-01-01 to 2025-01-31.csv')\n\nprint(f\"Shape after feature engineering: {df.shape}\")\ndf.head()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-19T10:09:08.076326Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-19T10:09:08.076658Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-19T10:09:15.444903Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-19T10:09:08.076633Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-19T10:09:15.444351Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Shape after feature engineering: (3265473, 34)\n","output_type":"stream"},{"execution_count":4,"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":"  tpep_pickup_datetime tpep_dropoff_datetime  passenger_count  trip_distance  \\\n0  2025-01-01 00:18:38   2025-01-01 00:26:59              1.0           1.60   \n1  2025-01-01 00:32:40   20